args:
The party heads to Felicia's home. Along the
way, Thanatos curses Cleo, trying to steal away
Felicia in exchange for her life. But Cleo is able
to recover once Phantom releases the curse.
The group then enters battle with more of
Thanatos's underlings.
Think that was the last of 'em?
Yeah, I think we're good for now.
I'm sorry I put you in so much danger.
Think nothing of it. Everyone's okay.
Right then. Let's get ourselves situated\nand set off for Felicia's village.
And so, the party proceeded toward\nFelicia's village without issue.
And without noticing the pair of glittering eyes\ngazing after them from afar...
The sun's already gone down.\nLet's set up camp here for the night.
What is it, Cleo? You look rather low.
It's hard to explain, but my body feels...\nheavy. I imagine it's nothing a good\nnight's sleep won't cure.
*yawn* Yeah, I'm more bushed\nthan a hedge maze!
I know we need rest, but we also need\nto have someone stand watch.
By yourself? Is that really a good idea?
He is correct, Felicia. You are our\nassailant's objective, after all.
Even so, I have to help SOMEHOW.
It's all right. The rest of us can take shifts.
Fair enough. When it's time to swap,\ncome kick me outta bed, yeah?
Felicia, nothing good will come of\nyou being this tense.
Oh dear. How did you know?
Because you're staring into the night\nwith a terrified look in your eyes.
To be honest, I've been hearing the\nvoice of Thanatos this entire time.
Now that you mention it, I also heard a\nvoice coming from the fiend horde.
Yes, although this is the first time\nit has been audible to other people.
I don't think Phantom has been able\nto hear it up to this point.
But I just keep hearing him...
Felicia... Oh, my sweet Felicia...\nWhy have you gone and left me...?
Your movements are beauty. They breathe\nnew life into my cracked and broken heart.\nNow...dance for me!
You are the light of hope itself!\nComfort in an isolated world of night!
I shall never let you go, for you are\nthe single ray of light in my world...
...No. Since the fiend horde was defeated,\nhe has been silent.
I'm sorry. Things are getting better,\nyet still my mind dwells in dark places.
That's not surprising, actually.\nStill, we should maybe...
Oh, I know! Why don't you tell me\nsomething about your village?
Whenever I feel down, I like to talk about\nfriends, family, and home.
Yes, I suppose I can see that.
The people in my village love festivals,\nwhich makes it a lively and fun place.
Even the most minor of events is cause\nfor a festival, but the one we hold for\nthe harvest lasts for days.
Then we... Er, {player_name}?\nIs something on my face?
Oh, sorry! I guess I was just glad\nto finally see you smiling.
Heh. I suppose I haven't done that\nin quite some time.
It's all thanks to you and your friends.
Peeping is such a tawdry act.
I was doing no such thing.\nI merely woke up unexpectedly.
Let's stop off in this village\nand replenish our supplies.
I will go and get us provisioned.\nEveryone else can rest here.
Wait. If you're going to get provisions,\nI should—
Cleo, you're clearly not feeling well.\nStay here. I have this.
No, I'm fine now. I just... Urrrgh...
Elisanne! Luca! Go find somewhere\nsafe for her to rest!
The heck's going on with you, girl?!
Cleo! Say somethin'! Somebody get water\nor a compress or whatever!
The curse of death feeds upon\nthis woman's life force.
If you do not return my dancer,\nI will take this life in recompense.
Oh no... This...this is all my fault!
Felicia, where are you going?! FELICIA!
Stop this, Thanatos! Release that woman!
This one is but a vessel for my voice.\nOh, my beloved Felicia...
Thanks to the actions of that loathsome\ndragon, I am unable to leave my realm.
I wished to come and meet you myself,\nbut that is now impossible.
Felicia, return with my messenger...\nReturn to the space between worlds.
When you do so, I will release the woman\nfrom her curse. All I need is you...
If it is your desire, it will be done.\nNow come unto me...
I'm sorry to have made you worry.\nBut as you can see, I am fine.
Of all the preposterous... Why?!\nWhat broke my curse?!
I drew out all of your black mana.
You use this wicked force to birth fiends\nand steal life itself...
Yet I am the same as you, Thanatos.\nBlack mana is no more poison to me\nthan the very air!
Rrrgh! Go, my servant! Annihilate these\nwretches and return my dancer!
